# Markdown hard line breaks are two trailing spaces, which git's default
# `blank-at-eol` whitespace check flags as errors. markdownlint (MD009,
# br_spaces=2) is the authority for markdown trailing whitespace, so exempt
# markdown from the raw check while keeping blank-at-eof and space-before-tab.
*.md whitespace=-blank-at-eol

# Pinned CDN asset fixtures (quartz/components/tests/fixtures/cdn-assets) are
# byte-exact mirrors captured from assets.turntrout.com so (screenshot)
# baselines don't depend on the live CDN. Treat them as opaque binary: git
# must not normalize EOLs or run whitespace checks, or the served bytes would
# diverge from what the baselines were captured against.
quartz/components/tests/fixtures/cdn-assets/** -text -diff
